image_analysis.description: A photograph showing a narrow storage closet or alcove with four wooden shelves. The shelves are supported by metal wall-mounted brackets. There are seven clear plastic storage bins with black handles and white labels on the shelves. The top shelf has one bin, and the three shelves below each have two bins. The bins appear to contain folded clothing or textiles. A single light bulb is mounted on the left wall. A light switch is visible on the far left wall. The floor is a light-colored tile or linoleum.
image_analysis.layout: Vertical orientation showing a storage area from a straight-on perspective.

notes: The text on the individual bin labels is visible but too small and blurry to read accurately. The primary text is the Bates stamp at the bottom right.
